text: Long before the evil Queen Ravenna was thought vanquished by Snow White's blade, she watched silently as her sister, Freya, suffered a heartbreaking betrayal and fled their kingdom. With Freya's ability to freeze any enemy, the young ice queen has spent decades in a remote wintry palace raising a legion of deadly huntsmen ‚Äì including Eric and warrior Sara ‚Äì only to find that her prized two defied her one demand: Forever harden your hearts to love.  When Freya learns of her sister's demise, she summons her remaining soldiers to bring the Magic Mirror home to the only sorceress left who can harness its power. But once she resurrects her sister Ravenna from its golden depths, the wicked sisters threaten this enchanted land with twice the darkest force it's ever seen. Now, their amassing army shall prove undefeatable‚Ä¶unless the banished huntsmen who broke their queen's cardinal rule can fight their way back to one another.

When Freya learns of her sister's demise, she summons her remaining soldiers to bring the Magic Mirror home to the only sorceress left who can harness its power. text: The only thing I disliked about this movie is that they focused too much time and story on "the good guys"/the good guy squad. And while they were the ones I was rooting for in the first movie, they were quite dull here. I wished there was more screen time and more of a story revolving around the queens and perhaps   (SPOILER ALERT DON'T READ THIS SEPARATE PIECE OF TEXT HERE IF MOVIE NOT SEEN not have them turn against each other or at least not so soon)   END SPOILER ALERT  Because that just took so much time away which would've been much more interesting to have seen spent on the sisters working together and owning the kingdom. The heroes in this story kind of bored me. The huntsman with the "stronger" witch would've also been fun to have seen, I think they've got a nice dynamic, but unfortunately much of that wasn't in there either.    Long story short: I'd like the movie to have spent more time on the witches/sisters/queens and even on the huntsman and *the* queen (not the ice queen). And maybe have the ice queen be a little more charismatic, I know she's like this for a reason, but in my opinion I'd just have liked to have seen her to be more like the other one (Ravenna).   Other than that I liked it. Perhaps they might/could implement some of that stuff I wrote into the next movie? That'd be great (at least for me).
